special' souls to greatness? <br /><br />Sanatani's The Little Light answers these questions through a series of dialogues with the nine planets in a 'planet party' that takes place in the Cosmic Womb. The imagination that went into the idea is beyond words, beyond time and beyond any book that I've ever read. In its pages, I found an indescribable sense of peace that I had been searching for. A peace that can only come after the madness of war. This book made me see that there is meaning behind the madness of it all. There is a reason. A reason that will only make sense in hindsight. We are not privy to this knowledge till we are ready to receive it. We must undergo the journey and trust that it will all make sense at the end. <br /><br />The most inspiring character in the book is the Little Light itself. I know you're going to say that protagonists usually are, but in this case--the supporting characters are the nine planets themselves! The Little Light is an unusual protagonist. When we first meet 'it' in the Cosmic Womb, it has neither a gender nor a body. It is simply a 'little light' that has emanated from the Great Light. Embedded in this Little Light is a burning desire and a great destiny. As the story goes on, the Little Light takes on human qualities and traits as it readies itself for life on planet earth.<br /><br />Reincarnation is a strong theme in the book. We do not come into this world empty-handed and nor do we leave it the same way. A soul has embedded within it countless memories, relationships and karma that it carries with it lifetime after lifetime. It is like a symphony of familiar songs that is etched in one's soul; and with each lifetime we progress and carry forward the work of previous lifetimes till it culminates in a great destiny. A great destiny that was owed to it well before it was born. <br /><br />For me, the most memorable aspect in the book is the Little Light. A fascinating soul--both incredibly young and enduring ancient. Her words, her questions, her quest--they healed my weary and tired soul. <br /><br />Thank you, Dipa--for writing such a wonderful book. It is my hope that this book gives your gift of healing to other souls just like myself.</span></div></div></div></section></section><section class="ReviewCard__tags"><span class="TruncatedItems TruncatedItems--span"><span class="TruncatedItems__item TruncatedItems__item--visible"><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/122572740?shelf=death" class="Button Button--tag-inline Button--small"><span class="Button__labelItem">death</span></a></span><span class="TruncatedItems__item TruncatedItems__item--visible"><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/122572740?shelf=reincarnation" class="Button Button--tag-inline Button--small"><span class="Button__labelItem">reincarnation</span></a></span><span class="TruncatedItems__item TruncatedItems__item--visible"><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/122572740?shelf=spirituality" class="Button Button--tag-inline Button--small"><span class="Button__labelItem">spirituality</span></a></span></span></section><footer class="SocialFooter"><div data-testid="stats" class="SocialFooter__statsContainer"><div class="Button__container"><button type="button" class="Button Button--inline Button--small Button--subdued"><span class="Button__labelItem">16 likes</span></button></div><div class="Button__container"><button type="button" class="Button Button--inline Button--small Button--subdued"><span class="Button__labelItem">3 comments</span></button></div></div><div data-testid="actions"><div class="SocialFooter__action"><div class="Button__container"><button type="button" class="Button Button--inline Button--small"><span class="Button__labelItem"><i class="Icon LikeIcon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M14.4813282,6.41129383 L14.586127,6.97676447 C14.5964421,7.03541935 14.6071117,7.09675198 14.6181364,7.1607667 L14.8551301,8.60363442 L17.440983,8.60363442 C18.1623576,8.60363442 18.821818