e. Her story, however, is profound. <br /><br />Books in the spirituality genre are usually heavy, airy-fairy or difficult to understand; which is truly bizarre considering that spirituality encompasses humans from all walks of life and not merely the learned men. Mythology was a focal point of oral storytelling in the ancient world. These days, these stories are relegated to the dusty books which only academics and the learned man read. <br /><br />I am more of a school-of-life type of guy. I learn from stories, not books. And Sanatani is a gifted storyteller and a spiritual leader. While this book is narrated as a fictional story--one that is suitable for both young adults and grown men--I found it deeply wise in discussing real-world human issues that have plagued humans from the dawn of time. In an age where so many young people grow up on a diet of nonsense for the mind, Sanatani dares to write a spirituality book that can appeal to all ages. I loved this book. It is a story the entire family can enjoy. <br /><br />I was particularly fond of the character of Saturn, who reminds me so much of myself in my older years. In Mercury, you will find your most beloved teenage child who humours you with his antics and wise cracks. It is the story of a family--one that loves, fights and makes up in the end to do what is right. As I read The Little Light, I had a sense that I was rediscovering a long lost friend that I have known for a long long time. This book left a mark of wonderment deep down in my soul--one that I will cherish and pass down to my children and grandchildren. <br /><br />For those who are ready, this book will awaken and enlighten your soul. For those who enjoy innovative stories, The Little Light will leave you in awe at the way this book is conceptualised and executed. It is a book unlike any other that will linger in your mind for the rest of your life...and the lifetimes to come. <br /><br />Thank you, Ms. Sanatani, for sharing your imagination with the world. May this book go on to inspire mankind for generations to come.</span></div></div></div></section></section><section class="ReviewCard__tags"><span class="TruncatedItems TruncatedItems--span"><span class="TruncatedItems__item TruncatedItems__item--visible"><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/122569372?shelf=death" class="Button Button--tag-inline Button--small"><span class="Button__labelItem">death</span></a></span><span class="TruncatedItems__item TruncatedItems__item--visible"><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/122569372?shelf=reincarnation" class="Button Button--tag-inline Button--small"><span class="Button__labelItem">reincarnation</span></a></span></span></section><footer class="SocialFooter"><div data-testid="stats" class="SocialFooter__statsContainer"><div class="Button__container"><button type="button" class="Button Button--inline Button--small Button--subdued"><span class="Button__labelItem">16 likes</span></button></div></div><div data-testid="actions"><div class="SocialFooter__action"><div class="Button__container"><button type="button" class="Button Button--inline Button--small"><span class="Button__labelItem"><i class="Icon LikeIcon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M14.4813282,6.41129383 L14.586127,6.97676447 C14.5964421,7.03541935 14.6071117,7.09675198 14.6181364,7.1607667 L14.8551301,8.60363442 L17.440983,8.60363442 C18.1623576,8.60363442 18.8218187,9.01120377 19.1444272,9.65642083 L19.1708204,9.70920723 C19.4523479,10.2722622 19.4523479,10.9350066 19.1708204,11.4980616 L19.118034,11.6036344 L19.1708204,11.7092072 C19.4523479,12.2722622 19.4523479,12.9350066 19.1708204,13.4980616 L19.118034,13.6036344 L19.1708204,13.7092072 C19.4523479,14.2722622 19.4523479,14.9350066 19.1708204,15.4980616 L19,15.8397024 L19,16.1036344 C19,16.7361314 18.6701344,17.3185188 18.1373501,17.6453922 L17.9472136,17.7480616 C17.4795438,17.9818965 16.9638538,18.1036344 16.440983,18.1036344 L9.66834148,18.1034086 C9.31027068,18.6437214 8.69