u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eIn The Little Light, Sanatani narrates the sojourn of a soul's journey in between life and death. It is written as a dialogue between 'The Little Light' and the planets. A wise and curious soul quizzes and questions the Nine Great Celestial Beings who all have nuggets of wisdom to offer--in their own idiosyncratic way, of course. The book is filled with memorable words of wisdom that will linger in your soul long after you finish reading it. One reading is simply not enough. This is one of those rare books that gets better the more times you read it. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eI chanced upon The Little Light when I was going through a particularly difficult and dark time in my life. Fear of death, fear of what happens in the wake of death, fear of what happens to our loved ones after we pass--all of these elements play a big role in the human psyche's fear of an inevitable chapter of all of our lives. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eIn this book, there is humour, depth and profound wisdom. It deals with the darkest moments in life without losing sight of the deep love that the Creator--which the author calls The Great Light--has for all of creation. The Little Light is a book that will bring peace to your heart and light to your soul.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThank you, Dipa Sanatani, for sharing your gift of words with the world. It is a truly a rare soul that possesses the gift to heal the world with words that come from deepest recesses of the heart. ","rating":5,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/122565906?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3587384186"},"likeCount":18,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":1,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:122572740":{"id":122572740,"__typename":"User","legacyId":122572740,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compre