here is meaning behind the madness of it all. There is a reason. A reason that will only make sense in hindsight. We are not privy to this knowledge till we are ready to receive it. We must undergo the journey and trust that it will all make sense at the end. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThe most inspiring character in the book is the Little Light itself. I know you're going to say that protagonists usually are, but in this case--the supporting characters are the nine planets themselves! The Little Light is an unusual protagonist. When we first meet 'it' in the Cosmic Womb, it has neither a gender nor a body. It is simply a 'little light' that has emanated from the Great Light. Embedded in this Little Light is a burning desire and a great destiny. As the story goes on, the Little Light takes on human qualities and traits as it readies itself for life on planet earth.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eReincarnation is a strong theme in the book. We do not come into this world empty-handed and nor do we leave it the same way. A soul has embedded within it countless memories, relationships and karma that it carries with it lifetime after lifetime. It is like a symphony of familiar songs that is etched in one's soul; and with each lifetime we progress and carry forward the work of previous lifetimes till it culminates in a great destiny. A great destiny that was owed to it well before it was born. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eFor me, the most memorable aspect in the book is the Little Light. A fascinating soul--both incredibly young and enduring ancient. Her words, her questions, her quest--they healed my weary and tired soul. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThank you, Dipa--for writing such a wonderful book. It is my hope that this book gives your gift of healing to other souls just like myself.","rating":5,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/122572740?shelf=read"},"taggings"