hat meets the planets before it is born. Through the modern retelling of ancient myths, Sanatani discusses many questions that humans have contemplated for eons. Her language is simple. Her story, however, is profound. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eBooks in the spirituality genre are usually heavy, airy-fairy or difficult to understand; which is truly bizarre considering that spirituality encompasses humans from all walks of life and not merely the learned men. Mythology was a focal point of oral storytelling in the ancient world. These days, these stories are relegated to the dusty books which only academics and the learned man read. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eI am more of a school-of-life type of guy. I learn from stories, not books. And Sanatani is a gifted storyteller and a spiritual leader. While this book is narrated as a fictional story--one that is suitable for both young adults and grown men--I found it deeply wise in discussing real-world human issues that have plagued humans from the dawn of time. In an age where so many young people grow up on a diet of nonsense for the mind, Sanatani dares to write a spirituality book that can appeal to all ages. I loved this book. It is a story the entire family can enjoy. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eI was particularly fond of the character of Saturn, who reminds me so much of myself in my older years. In Mercury, you will find your most beloved teenage child who humours you with his antics and wise cracks. It is the story of a family--one that loves, fights and makes up in the end to do what is right. As I read The Little Light, I had a sense that I was rediscovering a long lost friend that I have known for a long long time. This book left a mark of wonderment deep down in my soul--one that I will cherish and pass down to my children and grandchildren. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eFor those who are ready, this book will awaken and enlighten your soul. For those who enjoy innovative stories, The Little Light will leave you in awe at the way this book is conceptualised and executed. It is a book unlike any other that will linger in your mind for the rest of your life...and the lifetimes to come. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThank you, Ms. Sanatani, for sharing your imagination with the world. May this book go on to inspire mankind for generations to come.","rating":5,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/122569372?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"death","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/122569372?shelf=death"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"reincarnation","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/122569372?shelf=reincarnation"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3587481532"},"likeCount":16,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":0,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"User:122672921":{"id":122672921,"__typename":"User","legacyId":122672921,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1602265858i/122672921._UY200_CR50,0,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":false,"textReviewsCount":2,"viewableName":"David","isBlockedByViewer":false,"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/122672921-david","contributor":null,"isFollowing":false,"isFriend":false,"followersCount":0},"Review:kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.8vAY3nvUM2vDxOk7YGdpdQ":{"id":"kca://review:goodreads/amzn1.gr.review:goodreads.v1.8vAY3nvUM2vDxOk7YGdpdQ","__typename":"Review","book":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.7jgOdtvWnEGrInOV0xu8yQ"},"creator":{"__ref":"User:122672921"},"recommendFor":null,"updatedAt":1611553030595,"createdAt":1602267290864,"spoilerStatus":false,"lastRevisionAt":1602267924449,"text":"The highest form of expression for any artist is the act of devotion. When art is no longer about expressing the individual self,